# React component conventions

## Structure

- Functional components only, exported as named exports.
- Use `forwardRef` when the component exposes a DOM element (see `VideoPanel`).
- Define `Props` interface inline above the component, not in a shared file.
- Name callback props `onVerb` (e.g. `onSwitch`, `onPlayVariant`, `onSubmit`).

## CollapsiblePanel wrapper

Every detail section in the right column is wrapped in `CollapsiblePanel`:

```tsx
<CollapsiblePanel title="Section Name" count={items.length}>
  <MyComponent ... />
</CollapsiblePanel>
```

Pass `defaultOpen={false}` for sections that should start collapsed (e.g. Raw Manifest).

## Track-list component pattern

Components that show HLS track data follow a two-section layout:

1. **Runtime controls** — shown when `hasPlayer && runtimeTracks.length > 0`. Use `<button className="track-item">` for interactive items.
2. **Manifest info** — shown when manifest groups exist. Use `<div className="track-item track-item--info">` for non-interactive display.

Props always include: `manifestGroups`, `runtimeTracks`, `currentTrack`, `onSwitch`, `hasPlayer`.

When neither section has data, return a `<p className="notice">` with a short message.

## Badges

Use `.badge` with a color modifier for metadata pills:

- `badge--live` (red) — playing / live
- `badge--vod` (green) — VOD / auto
- `badge--event` (amber) — event / forced
- `badge--default` (blue) — default / active
- `badge--encrypted` (amber) — encryption
